-Could you water my plants?

103
00:12:03,360 --> 00:12:05,880
-Sure, I can do that.
-Morning and evenenings?

104
00:12:06,080 --> 00:12:07,560
Cool.

105
00:12:08,400 --> 00:12:12,520
Here's my carkeys. Use the
car as much as you want.

106
00:12:15,720 --> 00:12:18,400
Give them water so they can grow!

107
00:13:33,240 --> 00:13:34,720
Excuse me!

108
00:13:35,120 --> 00:13:36,960
Hello!

109
00:13:39,720 --> 00:13:41,480
Excuse me!

110
00:13:42,600 --> 00:13:44,480
A beer please!

111
00:13:49,320 --> 00:13:52,120
-Excuse me, but is that a sun?
-What?

112
00:13:54,040 --> 00:13:57,320
-Is it a sun on your amulet?
-No, it's a moon.

113
00:14:01,200 --> 00:14:03,520
Excuse me! Could I get a....

114
00:14:08,680 --> 00:14:11,200
The next song is a love song.

115
00:14:11,400 --> 00:14:14,840
About love that defies all boundaries.

116
00:14:57,600 --> 00:15:01,960
Hey, do you know of any cheap
places to spend the night?

117
00:15:02,200 --> 00:15:05,840
I'm from Berlin. 
I'm not familiar with this place.

118
00:15:08,720 --> 00:15:10,360
No? Ok.

119
00:15:14,520 --> 00:15:17,640
Excuse me, wait just a moment.

120
00:15:18,000 --> 00:15:19,880
I was a little far-off, -

121
00:15:20,080 --> 00:15:21,880
but I just remembered...

122
00:15:22,080 --> 00:15:25,440
that it is a cheap youth shelter nearby.

123
00:15:25,640 --> 00:15:29,120
If you want to, I can show you the way?

124
00:15:29,840 --> 00:15:33,080
-If it isn't to much trouble for you?
-Oh, no, I've got a car.

125
00:15:33,280 --> 00:15:35,960
-That is kind of you.
-My car is just over there.

126
00:15:37,240 --> 00:15:40,240
-I'm Daniel.
-Melek.

127
00:15:40,440 --> 00:15:43,280
-Lovely name. Where is it from?
-Turky.

128
00:15:43,480 --> 00:15:45,160
Are you turkish?

129
00:15:47,080 --> 00:15:49,800
-Do you want me to carry that for you?
-Thank you, it's ok.

130
00:15:50,000 --> 00:15:55,000
-It's not heavy.
-No, but you've been carrying it all day.

131
00:15:58,800 --> 00:16:02,200
-Are you hungry?
-Yes.

132
00:16:05,160 --> 00:16:07,160
It cant be true!

133
00:16:12,400 --> 00:16:16,560
This is Istanbul. Bosporus.
Europe to the left, Asia to the right.

134
00:16:16,760 --> 00:16:20,160
Some times I stand under the bridge
at night, to look at the water.

135
00:16:20,360 --> 00:16:23,040
When the moon shines at the
water surface, it looks like -

136
00:16:23,240 --> 00:16:28,400
thousands of little fish dancing.
In turkish we say -

137
00:16:28,600 --> 00:16:30,560
"Yakamoz"

138
00:16:33,240 --> 00:16:38,280
I've got a date under the bridge
friday at noon.

139
00:16:41,080 --> 00:16:43,120
Aren't you leaving for somewhere?

140
00:16:43,320 --> 00:16:46,640
-Aren't you leaving for somewhere?
-No, I don't think so.

141
00:16:46,840 --> 00:16:52,520
-But everyone leaves for vacation!
-Yeah, I know, but I want to stay here in Hamburg.

142
00:16:52,720 --> 00:16:58,800
Hamburg can be very nice during 
the summer. Parks, café's -

143
00:16:59,000 --> 00:17:02,600
and resturants and all.
And there's the beach!

144
00:17:02,800 --> 00:17:06,400
-Hamburg have a beach?
-Didn't you know? A real beach.

145
00:17:06,600 --> 00:17:11,040
With sand and water, and shells and stuff.

146
00:17:12,280 --> 00:17:14,360
Do you want to see it?

147
00:17:16,920 --> 00:17:18,400
The bill, please.

148
00:17:22,200 --> 00:17:27,240
Yes, well this is the beach.
Not that many shells, but...

149
00:17:27,960 --> 00:17:30,360
-Do you want a beer?
-Yes, please.

150
00:17:32,960 --> 00:17:37,200
Excuse me, could one of you sell me two beers?

151
00:17:37,400 --> 00:17:38,880
Sure.

152
00:17:42,040 --> 00:17:43,400
-Here you go.
-Thank you.

153
00:17:43,600 --> 00:17:48,320
-Wait! How much do I owe you?
-The best in life is free.

154
00:17:49,800 --> 00:17:51,240
Cheers.

155
00:18:01,440 --> 00:18:05,080
I'm starting to understand
why you don't want to leave.

156
00:18:07,640 --> 00:18:13,440
My sun, my moon, let your rays shine

157
00:18:14,800 --> 00:18:20,000
my sand warm

158
00:18:23,320 --> 00:18:29,160
I touch your skin with my wind

159
00:18:30,640 --> 00:18:35,880
my lips craves yours

160
00:18:39,280 --> 00:18:43,760
your eyes

161
00:18:46,400 --> 00:18:51,560
must never stop looking after me

162
00:18:54,600 --> 00:18:59,160
your lips

163
00:19:01,880 --> 00:19:06,960
must never stop kissing me.

164
00:19:19,640 --> 00:19:22,920
So, your name...Melek,
does it mean something?

165
00:19:23,680 --> 00:19:25,160
Angel.

166
00:19:26,720 --> 00:19:31,560
-You wear the name well.
-Thanks, but you don't know me.

167
00:19:37,440 --> 00:19:40,040
What about that place 
to spend the night?

168
00:19:49,040 --> 00:19:51,560
Do you live here alone?

169
00:19:52,480 --> 00:19:53,800
Yes.

170
00:19:55,000 --> 00:19:57,240
Don't you have a girlfriend?

171
00:19:59,120 --> 00:20:00,440
Nope.

172
00:20:03,120 --> 00:20:05,920
-Do you want some tea?
-Yes, please.

173
00:20:08,000 --> 00:20:12,440
It's so peculiar that we met
each other today, since...

174
00:20:13,480 --> 00:20:16,400
I knew that we were going to meet today.

175
00:20:16,720 --> 00:20:20,720
Maybe I didn't know, but just hoped.

176
00:20:22,320 --> 00:20:26,720
It's like you could decide
your own destiny in one day.

177
00:20:27,320 --> 00:20:30,840
I stood there and waited and
waited, for you, and...

178
00:20:31,880 --> 00:20:34,480
So I didn't believe that you
were going to show up.

179
00:20:37,560 --> 00:20:39,640
Then you stood there.

180
00:20:44,600 --> 00:20:46,240
Melek?

181
00:21:07,960 --> 00:21:11,040
-Thank you for everything.
-The pleasure was all mine.

182
00:21:11,240 --> 00:21:13,760
Good bye, Daniel.

183
00:21:42,520 --> 00:21:45,040
Bullshit!
Come to your senses and stay here!

184
00:21:45,240 --> 00:21:48,080
NO! I hate this fucking city!

185
00:21:48,280 --> 00:21:51,440
Yeah yeah, but where are you going?

186
00:21:51,640 --> 00:21:53,320
Where the wind takes me.

187
00:21:53,520 --> 00:21:57,360
-What do you mean by that?
-I just want to get away!

188
00:21:57,960 --> 00:22:01,280
The first car that stops,
decides my destination.

189
00:22:01,560 --> 00:22:05,280
What if the first car is going to Bayern?

190
00:22:05,680 --> 00:22:08,720
Do you want to stay in Bayern?

191
00:22:13,640 --> 00:22:16,720
So this will be my destiny, I guess.

192
00:22:21,960 --> 00:22:25,360
-I'm going to miss you.
-I'll miss you too.

193
00:22:41,000 --> 00:22:42,720
Hey, July.

194
00:22:46,160 --> 00:22:48,240
Jump in, I'm in a hurry.

195
00:23:06,200 --> 00:23:09,840
-Is this your car?
-No, it belongs to a friend of mine.

196
00:23:11,320 --> 00:23:13,680
Where do you want me to drive you?

197
00:23:15,000 --> 00:23:16,880
Where are you going?

198
00:23:17,080 --> 00:23:19,320
Istanbul

199
00:23:19,760 --> 00:23:21,360
Istanbul?

200
00:23:23,280 --> 00:23:25,320
Why are you going to Istanbul?

201
00:23:27,120 --> 00:23:28,880
It worked!

202
00:23:29,440 --> 00:23:31,040
What worked?

203
00:23:31,240 --> 00:23:32,840
The lucky ring.

204
00:23:33,040 --> 00:23:36,120
I know it sounds crazy and
illogical, but it worked.

205
00:23:37,400 --> 00:23:38,920
So where is she now?

206
00:23:39,120 --> 00:23:42,280
She flew to Turky on vacation this morning.

207
00:23:42,480 --> 00:23:48,760
Everything I know, is that she'll be 
waiting under the Bosporus bridge, friday at noon.

208
00:23:49,720 --> 00:23:52,400
July, she is so....

209
00:23:53,400 --> 00:23:56,320
-By the way, where are you going?
-What?

210
00:23:56,520 --> 00:23:59,560
I mean,  where are you off to?

211
00:24:02,680 --> 00:24:05,200
-I'm also going to Turky.
-What?

212
00:24:06,920 --> 00:24:08,960
To Istanbul.

213
00:24:18,600 --> 00:24:20,280
It's like this:

214
00:24:20,480 --> 00:24:23,160
Every summer, I stand there
where you picked me up -

215
00:24:23,360 --> 00:24:27,520
to leave on vacation.
I go wherever the wind takes me.

216
00:24:27,720 --> 00:24:31,320
The first person that picks me up,
decides where I'm going. You understand?

217
00:24:31,520 --> 00:24:33,880
-You do this every summer?
-Yes!

218
00:24:34,320 --> 00:24:39,040
I've been in the most odd places.
Italia, Spain...

219
00:24:39,400 --> 00:24:43,360
One guy brought me to Afghanistan.
Quite some place to travel to!

220
00:24:43,760 --> 00:24:45,760
-Afghanistan?
-Yes!

221
00:24:45,960 --> 00:24:47,760
-Amazing!
-Yeah.

222
00:24:47,960 --> 00:24:53,320
You never know where you end up.
It's like buying a surprise pack.

223
00:24:53,640 --> 00:24:58,000
-I see.
-And this year it'll be Turky. Awesome!

224
00:24:58,200 --> 00:25:01,640
I've never been in Turky.
This will be so cool.

225
00:25:01,840 --> 00:25:03,360
Definitely.

226
00:25:12,400 --> 00:25:14,520
